  "text": "The CODEOWNERS infrastructure in grafana/grafana comprises GitHub ownership definition, CI validation, and manifest generation components:\n\n**GitHub Configuration:**\n- `.github/CODEOWNERS` (1316 lines): The primary GitHub ownership definition file listing Grafana teams and their code ownership patterns.\n- `.github/workflows/codeowners-validator.yml` (44 lines): CI workflow using mszostok/codeowners-validator to validate CODEOWNERS syntax, detect unowned patterns, and catch duplicate patterns on every pull request.\n\n**JavaScript Manifest Generation Scripts:**\nThe `scripts/codeowners-manifest/` directory orchestrates complete manifest generation with caching:\n- `index.js` (101 lines): Main entry point that coordinates raw audit generation, manifest processing, and metadata caching. Implements cache validation using SHA-256 hashes of repository files and CODEOWNERS file.\n- `generate.js` (100 lines): Processes raw audit JSONL data to produce three JSON manifests: teams.json (unique teams), teams-by-filename.json (files mapped to owners), and filenames-by-team.json (teams mapped to files).\n- `raw.js` (84 lines): Spawns github-codeowners CLI to audit the CODEOWNERS file and generate raw JSONL output with file ownership mappings.\n- `metadata.js` (61 lines): Generates metadata.json containing timestamps and SHA-256 hashes for cache validation.\n- `constants.js` (11 lines): Defines path constants for manifest artifacts.\n\n**Test Coverage and Configuration:**\n- `jest.config.codeowner.js` (118 lines): Jest configuration that filters test files by team ownership. Uses codeowners-manifest/filenames-by-team.json to collect coverage only for files owned by a specified TEAM_NAME environment variable. Generates per-team coverage reports.\n- `scripts/test-coverage-by-codeowner.js`: Script that runs Jest with team-specific configuration, enabling coverage analysis per codeowner.\n\n**npm Scripts (package.json):**\nOrchestration commands for manifest generation:\n- `codeowners-manifest`: Complete manifest generation (clean + raw + generate + metadata)\n- `codeowners-manifest:clean`: Remove and recreate manifest directory\n- `codeowners-manifest:generate`: Generate manifest files from raw audit\n- `codeowners-manifest:metadata`: Generate only metadata\n- `codeowners-manifest:raw`: Generate raw audit JSONL only\n- `test:coverage:by-codeowner`: Run tests and coverage for a specific team\n\n**Go Feature Management Types:**\n- `pkg/services/featuremgmt/codeowners.go` (36 lines): Defines the `codeowner` type as a string alias representing GitHub team/user references (e.g., @grafana/dataviz-squad). Contains 35 team constants used in feature flag ownership.\n- `pkg/services/featuremgmt/models.go` (127): FeatureFlag struct includes `Owner` field of type `codeowner` to track feature ownership.\n- `pkg/services/featuremgmt/feature_toggle_api/types.go` (33): FeatureSpec API type defines `Owner` field with JSON tag `codeowner` for API serialization of feature ownership.\n\nThe infrastructure creates a complete pipeline: CODEOWNERS file → validation workflow → raw audit generation → manifest creation with caching → team-based test coverage analysis and feature flag ownership tracking."
}

